<center><font size=7><b>Nightshade</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 4</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>here's a short program
that'll give you infinite lives on
<I>Nightshade</I> - and it's short
because Ultimate has given
Speedlock a miss this time
round.
<BR><BR>
<CODE>100 FOR x=1 to 5: LOAD &quot;&quot; CODE: NEXT x <BR>
110 POKE 53442,0: POKE 53443,12 <BR>
120 RANDOMIZE USR 23424</CODE>
<BR><BR>
	All you have to do is type in
the short Basic loader, run it and
play your master tape through
from the beginning. The original
Basic loader will now be
ignored.
 <i>(Dave Nicholls in Your Spectrum issue 20)</i> 

<br><hr>
<table border="0">
<tr>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>DESCRIPTION</B></U></TD>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>POKE(s)</B></U></TD>
</TR>
<tr><td>Infinite Lives</td><td>52190,50:52191,205:52192,187</td></tr>
<tr><td>Infinite Energy</td><td>52739,0</td></tr>
<tr><td>No nasties</td><td>52739,0</td></tr>
</table>
<BR><BR><U><B>IMPORTANT</b></U> - Some snapshots are saved with the title SCREEN$ intact. You MUST put these POKES in on the menu screen as the game code is all moved about.<BR>
I'd also like to say that I know that the way I've got the infinite lives is both "hacky" and crap, but I can't find any easier
way of doing it, so sorry :-)<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>(Gerard Sweeney in Hack Attack III)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Type-in hacks</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD><a href="http://www.users.globalnet.co.uk/~jimg/yr20/yr20_40.htm#Hacker">http://www.users.globalnet.co.uk/~jimg/yr20/yr20_40.htm#Hacker</a>&nbsp; <i>(Dave Nicholls in Your Spectrum issue 20)</i> 

<br><hr>
<pre>
10 LOAD ""CODE: LOAD ""CODE: LOAD ""CODE
20 POKE 23453,201: PRINT USR 23424
30 POKE 52665,33: POKE 52668,52: REM infinite lives
40 POKE 49228,20: REM run fast all the time
50 POKE 52900,0: POKE 52901,0: POKE 52902,0: REM see final screen when you die
60 POKE 23453,33: LOAD ""CODE: LOAD ""CODE
70 PRINT USR 23453
</pre>
 <i>(YS Smash Tips)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
</table></center><P>
